  "case": "sanfer_tunnel",
  "mode": "post_mortem",
  "timeline": [
    {
      "t_s": 0.24,
      "event": "Session begins. ublox_rover/navrelposned publishes flags=3 (gnssFixOk=1, diffSoln=1, relPosValid=0, carrSoln=none, relPosHeadingValid=0). RTK heading is unresolved from the very first sample.",
      "evidence": "ublox_rover_navrelposned.csv first row: flags_raw=3, carr_soln=none, rel_pos_valid=0, rel_pos_heading_valid=0"
    },
    {
      "t_s": 0.40,
      "event": "robot_localization EKF (ekf_se_map) reports ERROR: 'odometry/filtered topic status: No events recorded'. The map-frame fuser never publishes its output during the whole run.",
      "evidence": "diagnostics_nonzero_unique.csv level=2 at 0.40s"
    },
    {
      "t_s": 0.52,
      "event": "u-blox driver warnings on both receivers: 'TMODE3 Not configured' and 'fix topic status: Frequency too high'. Indicates the survey/time-mode and output-rate config pushed to the receivers does not match the expected dual-antenna moving-base profile.",
      "evidence": "diagnostics_nonzero_unique.csv level=1 at 0.52s for ublox_rover and ublox_moving_base"
    },
    {
      "t_s": 0.20,
      "event": "Drive-by-wire is NEVER enabled during the 3626.8 s session (brake.enabled and throttle.enabled remain 0 throughout). The run is a manual data-collection drive, not an autonomous incident.",
      "evidence": "brake_20hz.csv and throttle_20hz.csv each show a single 'enabled' state transition at t~0 -> 0 and no further transitions"
    },
    {
      "t_s": 148.33,
      "event": "First burst of /ntrip_client RTCM checksum mismatches (Expected vs Actual differ). NTRIP corrections stream becomes sporadically corrupt. Pattern recurs ~100 times through the session.",
      "evidence": "rosout_warnings.csv /ntrip_client 'Found packet, but checksums didn't match'"
    },
    {
      "t_s": 195.39,
      "event": "ublox_moving_base 'fix topic status' escalates to ERROR: 'Frequency too low.; Timestamps too far in past seen.' -- the moving-base receiver is skipping output and its timestamps drift.",
      "evidence": "diagnostics_nonzero_unique.csv level=2 at 195.39s"
    },
    {
      "t_s": 1664.17,
      "event": "ntrip_client socket timeout: 'Unable to send NMEA sentence to server.' After 5 failed sends it reconnects at 1684.20 s; during ~20 s of the gap the server serves 'RTCM requested before client was connected, returning empty list', so MB runs without corrections.",
      "evidence": "rosout_warnings.csv 1664.17 timeout, 1684.20 restart, 1684.23 empty RTCM list"
    },
    {
      "t_s": 3347.73,
      "event": "ntrip_client hard reconnect: 'RTCM data not received for 4 seconds, reconnecting' (rosout level=8). MB again briefly runs without corrections.",
      "evidence": "rosout_warnings.csv /ntrip_client level=8 at 3347.73s"
    },
    {
      "t_s": 3626.80,
      "event": "Session ends. Over the full log: 18133/18133 navrelposned samples carry carr_soln='none', rel_pos_valid=0 and rel_pos_heading_valid=0 -- i.e. the dual-antenna RTK heading NEVER achieved even a float solution. Rover diff_soln=1 only 15.0% of the time (2715/18133) while moving-base diff_soln=1 for 99.99% (16637/16639). MB receives corrections cleanly; rover does not.",
      "evidence": "ublox_rover_navrelposned.csv (carr_soln, rel_pos_valid columns), ublox_rover_navstatus.csv flags (221 off / 223 on bit1), ublox_moving_base_navstatus.csv flags (all 223)"
    },
    {
      "t_s": null,
      "event": "Secondary sensor fault: /vehicle/gps/fix (Dataspeed DBW NMEA GPS) reports latitude stuck at -3e-7 deg for all 3591 messages while longitude varies normally around -58.53 deg. The latitude field is effectively dead/mis-parsed for the entire run.",
      "evidence": "gps_fix.csv: lat range [-3e-7, -3e-7], lon range [-58.571, -58.507]"
    }
  ],
  "hypotheses": [
    {
      "id": "H1",
      "claim": "The moving-base -> rover RTCM observation link is not delivering data. The u-blox moving-base receiver is not outputting (or the rover is not ingesting) UBX-RXM-RAWX/SFRBX or RTCM3 4072.0/4072.1 + 1077/1087/1097/1127/1230 on its inter-receiver UART. Without the MB's raw observations the rover cannot form a carrier-phase baseline, so carr_soln is permanently 'none' and rel_pos_heading_valid=0 for the whole session.",
      "support": [
        "carr_soln='none' and rel_pos_valid=0 for 18133/18133 samples over 60 min -- a complete, not intermittent, failure.",
        "Moving base achieves diffSoln=1 essentially 100% of the time (16637/16639) -> MB is receiving RTCM from NTRIP correctly and is capable of producing a reference solution.",
        "Rover only shows diffSoln=1 15.0% of the time, consistent with it opportunistically picking up RTCM from NTRIP directly and NOT from the MB.",
        "u-blox driver diagnostic 'TMODE3 Not configured' fires on both receivers at startup, indicating the moving-base / rover role configuration never ran cleanly.",
        "Horizontal accuracy stays in the 0.47-1.30 m band characteristic of single-frequency/DGPS float, never the 1-3 cm band of RTK fixed."
      ],
      "contradictions": [
        "If the inter-receiver link were merely noisy we would expect occasional carr_soln=float spikes; we see zero. Therefore the failure mode is structural (unconfigured or unwired) rather than marginal."
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "H2",
      "claim": "NTRIP corruption / disconnects are the primary reason RTK never fixes (MB can't hand a clean enough stream to rover).",
      "support": [
        "~100 'Expected/Actual Checksum' mismatch lines in rosout from /ntrip_client.",
        "Hard reconnect events at 1664 s and 3347 s briefly starve the MB of corrections."
      ],
      "contradictions": [
        "The moving-base itself reports diffSoln=1 in 99.99% of samples, meaning the NTRIP stream is good enough for DGNSS at the MB. If NTRIP were the blocker the MB would also show frequent diffSoln drops.",
        "carr_soln=none is permanent and starts at t=0.24 s -- well before any NTRIP checksum errors at t=148 s. Checksum corruption cannot explain a failure that precedes it."
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "H3",
      "claim": "Antenna baseline is too short or antennas were swapped (ambiguity never resolves).",
      "support": [
        "Symptoms (carrSoln never float) are compatible with poor inter-antenna geometry.",
        "num_sv and h_acc remain healthy which suggests sky view is fine -- points to a baseline/mounting issue rather than signal occlusion."
      ],
      "contradictions": [
        "Even a short or swapped baseline will typically yield carrSoln=float within seconds once RTCM 4072 is flowing; we never see that happen once.",
        "Doesn't explain why rover's own diffSoln toggles so rarely while MB's is continuous."
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "H4",
      "claim": "Tunnel ingress dropped GNSS and broke RTK for the rest of the run.",
      "support": [
        "Case name 'sanfer_tunnel' suggests a tunnel traversal."
      ],
      "contradictions": [
        "fix_type stays at 3 (3D) for 18133/18133 rover samples with num_sv>=16 throughout; no tunnel-shaped gap.",
        "carr_soln is 'none' from t=0.24 s, before the vehicle even moves (speed_mps stays ~0 for the first 60 s). The failure precedes any possible tunnel event."
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "H5",
      "claim": "Dataspeed /vehicle/gps/fix latitude parser is the root fault.",
      "support": [
        "Latitude is stuck at -3e-7 deg for all 3591 messages."
      ],
      "contradictions": [
        "That topic is an auxiliary vehicle-mounted NMEA GPS and is not the localization source (ublox_rover is). It is a real defect but does not cause the RTK heading to fail.",
        "It should still be fixed, but it is a separate issue; noted as a secondary finding."
      ]
    }
  ],
  "root_cause_idx": 0,
  "patch_proposal": {
    "summary": "Re-enable the moving-base -> rover RTCM path. In the dual-antenna u-blox F9P setup the moving-base must publish UBX-RXM-RAWX/SFRBX (or equivalently RTCM3 4072.0, 4072.1, 1077, 1087, 1097, 1127, 1230) on its inter-receiver UART, and the rover must be configured to consume RTCM3 on the matching input UART at the same baud. The current logs show carr_soln='none' for 100% of the 60-minute session with MB receiving NTRIP corrections cleanly but rover only occasionally showing DGPS -- the classic fingerprint of a missing MB->rover link.",
    "changes": [
      {
        "file": "ublox_gps/config/moving_base.yaml",
        "change": "Under uart2: set out: [UBX-RXM-RAWX, UBX-RXM-SFRBX] OR out_protocol: RTCM3 with messages [4072.0@1, 4072.1@1, 1077@1, 1087@1, 1097@1, 1127@1, 1230@0.1]; baudrate: 460800; in_protocol: none. Ensure tmode3: DISABLED (0). Ensure publish.nav.relposned: false on MB and publish.nav.pvt: true at 5 Hz (the current diagnostics complain that MB 'fix topic' frequency is too high then too low -- clamp rate_hz to 5)."
      },
      {
        "file": "ublox_gps/config/rover.yaml",
        "change": "Under uart2: set in_protocol: RTCM3; baudrate: 460800 (must match MB). Ensure tmode3: DISABLED. Ensure cfg.dgnss_mode: RTK_FIXED (3) so the rover attempts fixed ambiguity resolution. publish.nav.relposned: true, publish.nav.heading: true."
      },
      {
        "file": "hardware/mb_rover_uart.md",
        "change": "Verify the physical cable between MB-UART2 and rover-UART2: TX of MB -> RX of rover, common GND, same baud. A swapped TX/RX here is a common cause of this exact failure signature."
      },
      {
        "file": "ntrip_client/config.yaml",
        "change": "Raise NMEA heartbeat to 1 Hz and lower the 'fail-then-reconnect' threshold from 5 missed sends to 2 so the 20 s dropout at 1664 s and the 4 s dropout at 3347 s recover faster. Also enable RTCM3 CRC-24Q validation and drop malformed packets silently instead of emitting ROS WARNs (log ~100 checksum-mismatch spams in this run)."
      },
      {
        "file": "ekf_se_map.yaml (robot_localization)",
        "change": "The map-frame EKF never published during this run (diagnostic 'No events recorded' at 0.40 s). Once RTK heading is restored, verify subscriptions to /ublox_rover/navheading and /ublox_rover/fix are correct and that two_d_mode/publish_tf/use_control are consistent with the dual-antenna heading input."
      },
      {
        "file": "dbw_mkz/nmea_gps_parser.cpp",
        "change": "Secondary finding: /vehicle/gps/fix latitude is stuck at ~-3e-7 deg for all 3591 msgs. Inspect the NMEA $GPGGA parsing path for lat (likely sign/hemisphere or DDMM.MMMM decimal handling bug). This is not the cause of the RTK failure but is a sensor-level defect."
      }
    ],
    "verification": [
      "After patch, in a static open-sky test the rover should achieve carr_soln=fixed (2) within 60 s and rel_pos_heading_valid=1 should stay at 1 for >=99% of samples.",
      "Repeat the Sanfer Tunnel route; expect carr_soln=fixed on approach, a brief fallback to carr_soln=float or none during the underground segment, and automatic re-acquisition to fixed within ~10 s of tunnel exit.",
      "Re-run the diagnostics; the 'TMODE3 Not configured' and 'fix topic status Frequency too low/high' entries should disappear.",
      "ekf_se_map should publish /odometry/filtered continuously (no more 'No events recorded')."
    ]
  }
}

